other_tests.findings: Left-sided slowing and attenuation, no epileptiform activity.
Decreased cerebral perfusion predominantly of the left frontoparietal cortex.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After dural arteriovenous fistula obliteration, left frontoparietal cortical perfusion improved, especially in the left dorsolateral prefrontal cortex.

other_tests.findings: Presence of a giant high flow dural arteriovenous fistula at the middle third of the superior sagittal sinus.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Follow-up angiogram showed obliteration of the anomaly.
